		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Oh by the way, many of the health beneifits that Phil Chandler talked about in honey is not available in the honey you buy at the grocery store. This honey is pasteurized, from what I have heard pretty much all of the health benefits in pasteurized honey have been wiped out. For those people with pollen allergies who take honey as medicine the honey should be from hives within 40 miles of where you live. BUY LOCAL HONEY! If you think about it local honey is like a flu shot for SOME of those who suffer with pollen allergies.</p>
</div>

