		<div class="comment-body"><p>Great job guys. </p>
<p>About 5 years ago I worked for a company that specialized in bee extermination/removal from people&#8217;s houses. It was only a summer job, but since I moved on, the company has completely changed the way they approach the issue of bee infestations in people&#8217;s homes. Everything they do now is a live &#8220;rescue&#8221;, where no bees are killed. Just simply removed and given to local beekeepers. </p>
<p>Haven&#8217;t started keeping any bees of my own yet, but definitely will once I am somewhere more permanent. </p>
<p>If you live in the southwest, several varieties of iceplants and other succulent groundcovers are BIG attractors for bees.</p>
